    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001108_0179"/>
        		<head>Jim to Mr Paul A. Rockwell <date value="1916-06-21">June 21 [1916]</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-06-21">June 21 [1916]</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Paul:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            You have doubtless
            heard of Balsley’s wound.
            Explosive bullet dangerously
            near  vitals.  Fragments
            have been taken out
            and danger is past.  He
            was caught between
            four Boches.  Landed back 
            of trenches, and was taken
            to a fort from which 
            place officers took him
            in auto to field Ambulance.
                        
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001108_0181" n="[p.2]"/>
            
            Take back everything
            I said about the poor
            boy.  He’s been very
            brave and decent during
            his suffering.
            </p><p>
            Chapman broke my
            machine for me yesterday
            and I’m out of it for
            24 hours or more.  Johnson
            was lost the other
            day and again this
            morning.  Been five hours
                        
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001108_0180" n="[p.3]"/>
            
            now since word of 
            him.
            </p><p>
            My sweet smelling
            friend of Viodak has
            moved to another branch.
            She’s at 41 Bd. Raspail
            as I was informed in 
            a note this morning.
            </p><p>
            Masson here with us
            now.  Interesting, serious
            chap.  Cowden trying for
            a month’s leave.  Strain
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001108_0181" n="[p.4]"/>
            
            too great for his
            delicate nerves.  Excuse
            rush but I’ve got
            to go over now and
            get my cuckoo where
            Victor left it 45 kilometers
            off.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>More anon.<lb/>
            My love to Mrs. Weeks.</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim</signed>
        		</closer>
        		
            
